    # game/areas/ford.rpy:306
    old "You move away from the creek, get on your feet, and unpack the tinderbox, the wooden stave, and the set of rags, as well as the oil. After you assemble a torch, you sit down on the ground, preparing the flint and the linen char cloth. Decades ago, before The Southern Invasion, people used fire strikers made of thick steel, but all you have is a cube-like piece of harsh pyrite. It’s not ideal, but good enough for a couple of sparks. \n\nHolding the fire, you get back in the saddle. You swing your weapon left and right - there isn’t as much smoke as you expected. "
    new ""

